input:
AITA for blocking Nick's mother out of Nick's life and refusing to give her a second chance? | So, this was about a couple years ago, but as of recently, Nick has been feeling guilty because of it.

&#x200B;

Nick should give some backstory first. Nick's mother wasn't the best person; she acted like she loved Nick sometimes, but a lot of the time she would be quite abusive in the emotional sense. For example, when Nick was learning how to drive she would constantly make comments about how Nick was purposely trying to harm and kill both her and Nick's sister by purposely trying to crash the car. Not only that, but she would constantly tell Nick how terrible of a person Nick is, how Nick was compliant with the "people" trying to "get" her, and she would use that as an excuse to punish Nick severely for weeks at a time. There's more, but Nick has trouble addressing this stuff.

&#x200B;

Eventually, Nick broke down and couldn't take it anymore. Nick wanted away from her as much as possible. Nick called Nick's dad, told him Nick wanted to move in with him and then proceeded to tell Nick's mother the same. Instead of becoming angry, she tried everything she could to keep Nick from leaving (preparing Nick's favorite meals every day, tried to enroll Nick in a new high school, begged Nick to not pack Nick's things, etc. Everything but apologize for how she treated Nick). Nick ended up agreeing to call every day while Nick lived with Nick's dad, but this didn't last long. While texting with Nick's sister, Nick ended up learning that it was Nick's mother pretending to be Nick's sister. After this Nick was done. Nick called Nick's mother, told her off and then ended by telling her Nick wanted nothing to do with her anymore. Nick blocked her number and Nick thought that was that.

&#x200B;

But as of recently, Nick's mother has been going to therapy and receiving medication for bipolar disorder. Nick keeps being told that she's doing better and that Nick should reach out and try to reconnect, if not for her sake, for Nick's sister's and Nick's grandfather's sake (Nick can't see them as much because of Nick's mother and Nick's grandfather is quite old and likely doesn't have many years left.) But Nick wants nothing to do with her anymore; she betrayed Nick's trust on several occasions as well as gave Nick longstanding problems with depression. But Nick feels a little conflicted. Nick feels as if Nick is the asshole for not giving her a second chance, or at least not having some relationship with her so Nick could spend more time with Nick's sister and grandfather, but yet Nick is still firm on Nick's decision to not want to have anything to do with her.

&#x200B;

So, Nick guesses Nick should ask you all, is Nick the asshole for not giving her the second chance or is Nick justified in not wanting to see her ever again. Most of Nick's family feel as if Nick should reach out, but Nick does mostly feel justified. Though, no one in Nick's family knows the full extent of the story, so that's why Nick is posting this here.

&#x200B;

To clarify: Nick is an adult now, but Nick was a teen when all of the shit initially happened and yes Nick's mother did try to force Nick back through the courts, but she failed. As well as it took Nick four days to pack and Nick's dad to come pick Nick up.
